@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 40
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  BorderColor #475569
}
skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor #DBEAFE
  BorderColor #1D4ED8
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #FEF3C7
  BorderColor #B45309
}
skinparam artifact {
  BackgroundColor #ECFCCB
  BorderColor #4D7C0F
}
skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #E0F2FE
  BorderColor #0369A1
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF7ED
  BorderColor #C2410C
}

title EduSecure Secure Deployment View

node "Student laptop / browser" as StudentDevice #E0F2FE

rectangle "A. Repository-proven local deployment" as LocalDev {
  node "Frontend dev server\nVite :5173" as FrontendDev

  node "Backend app\nSpring Boot bootRun :8080" as BackendDev {
    artifact "REST API + security controls" as DevApi
    artifact "Internal crypto services\n(auth, MFA, submissions, audit)" as DevCrypto
  }

  database "PostgreSQL :5432\npublished by dev compose" as PostgresDev
  database "MongoDB :27017\nshared-space chat store" as MongoDev
  artifact "Submission ciphertext store\nDocker volume" as SubmissionStoreDev
  artifact "Source bind mounts\nfrontend/ + backend/" as SourceMounts
}

rectangle "B. Intended secure production deployment" as Prod {
  cloud "Internet / untrusted network" as Internet

  node "OVH VPS public ingress\nNginx + Let's Encrypt + firewall" as Vps

  node "VPN tunnel\nOpenVPN / private upstream path\n10.8.0.1 <-> 10.8.0.2" as Vpn

  rectangle "Home server application boundary\nno home-router port forwarding" as HomeServer {
    node "Frontend container :3000\nstatic SPA, read-only FS" as FrontendProd

    node "Backend container :8080\nSpring Boot prod profile" as BackendProd {
      artifact "Internal auth / crypto / audit services" as ProdCrypto
    }

    database "PostgreSQL\ninternal Compose network only" as PostgresProd
    database "MongoDB\nCompose profile: chat" as MongoProd
    artifact "Encrypted submission store\n/srv/edusecure/data/submission-storage" as SubmissionStoreProd
    artifact "External signing keypair\n/run/edusecure/crypto:ro" as SigningKeys
  }
}

StudentDevice --> FrontendDev : http://localhost:5173
FrontendDev --> BackendDev : http://localhost:8080/api\ncredentialed requests + CSRF
BackendDev --> PostgresDev : JPA + Liquibase\nusers, MFA, grades, audit rows
BackendDev --> MongoDev : shared-space chat data\nwhen chat is enabled
BackendDev --> SubmissionStoreDev : AES-GCM ciphertext files
SourceMounts .. FrontendDev
SourceMounts .. BackendDev

StudentDevice --> Internet : https://edusecure.skey.ovh
Internet --> Vps : TLS 1.2/1.3\nHTTP->HTTPS redirect + HSTS
Vps --> Vpn : reverse proxy to private upstreams
Vpn --> FrontendProd : 10.8.0.2:3000
Vpn --> BackendProd : 10.8.0.2:8080/api
BackendProd --> PostgresProd : internal network only\nnot reverse-proxied publicly
BackendProd --> MongoProd : optional chat persistence\nmessage documents only
BackendProd --> SubmissionStoreProd : encrypted submissions at rest
BackendProd --> SigningKeys : ECDSA signing / verification material

note right of BackendDev
Repository-proven backend controls include:
- bcrypt password hashing
- JWT + HttpOnly auth cookie handling
- AES-GCM protection of MFA secrets
- AES-GCM encryption of stored submissions
- wrapped submission DEKs via AES key wrap
- SHA-256 hashing + ECDSA signature verification
- HMAC-backed MAC-chained audit integrity

These are internal backend services,
not a separate crypto microservice.
end note

note bottom of LocalDev
Interpretation boundary:
- local compose proves service separation, source-mounted dev workflow,
  and direct database/chat dependencies
- it does not by itself prove HTTPS enforcement, hardened cookies,
  router isolation, or VPN-only reachability
end note

note right of Vps
Public ingress controls:
- TLS termination with Let's Encrypt
- HTTP->HTTPS redirect
- HSTS + security headers
- centralised proxy logging / perimeter firewall
end note

note right of HomeServer
Production-side controls:
- frontend and backend run as immutable images
- backend uses SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod
- AUTH_COOKIE_SECURE=true and restricted CORS origin
- no-new-privileges on frontend/backend containers
- PostgreSQL and MongoDB remain off the public internet
- home-server firewall should allow only VPS tunnel IPs
end note

note bottom of MongoProd
Optional chat deployment path:
- enabled through APP_CHAT_ENABLED and Compose profile `chat`
- MongoDB stores shared-space chat documents
- when E2EE mode is enabled, backend accepts ciphertext payloads
  instead of plaintext message bodies
end note


@enduml

